1943;;The Ghost and the Guest;;American;;William Nigh;;Florence Rice, James Dunn;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Ghost_and_the_Guest;;Webster Frye (James Dunn) and his newly-wed wife Jackie (Florence Rice) travel to an old house in the country for their honeymoon. They begin to think the house is haunted, but it turns out that the house is being used as a gangster hideout.[1][2]